name: Tom Aspinall
summary: Amidst the headlines surrounding UFC 309, a back-and-forth between Jon Jones and Tom Aspinall has emerged. Jones has denied accusations of avoiding Aspinall, while Aspinall remains determined to face Jones for the undisputed UFC heavyweight title rather than Stipe Miocic. UFC President Dana White has stated that Jones would fight Aspinall next, dismissing a potential matchup with Alex Pereira. Despite Aspinall's absence from the Jones-Miocic press conference, he expressed confidence in a potential unification fight. However, Jones has set a condition for the bout, which has yet to be disclosed. As the hype for UFC 309 builds, Jones' list of excuses for not fighting Aspinall has drawn criticism, with some believing he deserves the blame for the lack of a matchup.

name: Miss Universe 2024 winner
summary: At the Miss Universe 2024 pageant, history was made as Victoria Kjær Theilvig of Denmark emerged as the first Miss Universe from her country. The event featured 125 contestants from around the globe, and the live updates and highlights of the competition were widely covered by media outlets. Victoria's victory marked a significant milestone for Denmark and the pageant itself. Alma Cooper, a soldier from Michigan who participated in the pageant, also garnered attention for her resilience and determination. The pageant's prestigious crown, adorned with valuable materials, became a topic of interest, sparking questions about its ownership and significance. Overall, the Miss Universe 2024 competition celebrated the achievements of women and showcased the diversity of beauty standards worldwide.

name: Jimmy Carter
summary: Former President Jimmy Carter has received his 10th Grammy nomination for his spoken-word album "Last Sundays in Plains." Carter, who is now 100 years old, is the first former president to reach this milestone. If he wins, he will become the oldest Grammy winner in history, surpassing Tony Bennett, who currently holds the record at 95 years old. Carter's nomination highlights his continued involvement in public life, including his work with the Carter Center, which promotes human rights and conflict resolution around the world.
